		<hr size="1">well, id day go with the beastlord class. for one, we can melee very well, have the use of some very nice weapons at mid-high lvls (some even nice at low lvls), and we can absorb dmg more than mages. dont get me wrong though, mages are great (have a 34 mage), but at higher lvls you want a pet class that will be able to take some dmg from mobs before pet takes back agro. plus side to mages are incredible pets with even better abilities for each type, insane nukes (at least i think they are insane, but hey, i never use nuke spells with my bst, hehe), as you mentioned CoH spell, and at higher lvls the spells to summon pet gear. they dont get many beneficial spells like bst's do (although the shielding spells are awesome), they usually dont need any seeing as how pet really does most of the work on a mob, and about 55-60% of the time in a group with a buffer. as for raids, mages are an excellent class because their pets can do some pretty good dmg, (they hit a lot harder than bst pets from what i can tell), and they can nuke for a lot at high lvls, but bst's can somewhat buff a raid group with the spiritual spells, and their pets can do some good dmg as well as well as the bst getting in there and meleeing and DoTing and nuking. well, hopefully this info helps you on your class decision, good luck.</P><P>Konsh Shell<BR>lvl 52 primalist<BR>Cazic-Thule server<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
