		<hr size="1">Well I am a fan of both Mages and BL's but a comparison between the two is very difficult. I have a 53 mage but have not played a BL. BL's and mages are on the top of my list for DPS in grind groups and mages ARE GREAT IN RAIDS. Not sure why Konsh is comparing MAge and BEast taking damage. As a pet class at higher levels you don't want to take damage, that is for the MA to take. He also says mages don't get many useful spells at higher levels, I disagree.</P><P>Mages have insane DPS with pet, nukes, Damage Sheilds and focus items given to others.</P><P>In raids my mage is VERY useful, I contribute huge amounts of damage even at lvl 53. I am also a walking general store that helps our raid a ton. Before raid I will summon arrows, higher level mages summon great pet gear, summon throwing weapons for our pullers, summon focus items that our nukers use which increases damage a lot. Eye of Zomm is hugely beneficial. Mod rods are also very helpful.</P><P>Point is both of these clsses are great DPS classes. If you like melee types more take BL. If you like caster classes and standing out because you are so helpful on raids and in grind groups play a mage.</P><P>I would really focus around the caster and melee type and what you would rather play. Again, both classes are excellent and I love to have Bth of them in grind groups for DPS, top of my list in the planes for DPS.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
